Yom Hazikaron - or Memorial Day - is held the day before Israel's independence day . 
  Theatres and cinemas are closed by law on the day and Israelis stand to attention for two minutes . 
  Remembrance ceremonies mark the 23,320 people who have died 'fighting for the national cause' since 1860 . 
  This year marks 67 years since the declaration of the state on May 14 . 
 